# Boltrope — environment template for the local / dev docker-compose stack.
# ============================================================================
# The compose file lives in deploy/, so `docker compose` reads deploy/.env. Copy
# this template there (the copy is git-ignored) and edit as needed:
#
#     cp .env.example deploy/.env
#
# EVERY variable below has a working default baked into deploy/docker-compose.yml,
# so an EMPTY .env already brings the stack up KEYLESS on the built-in `stub`
# provider (a deterministic, network-free demo model — no API key, no backend).
# You only need to set values to (a) talk to a real model (a hosted provider or a
# local OpenAI-compatible endpoint), (b) reach a sandbox on Linux, or (c) change
# ports/credentials.
#
# Two namespaces appear here:
#   * BOLTROPE_*  — consumed by the Boltrope binaries via the koanf config loader
#                   (flags > env > file > defaults). Nested keys use a DOUBLE
#                   underscore: BOLTROPE_SERVER__HTTP_ADDR -> server.http_addr.
#   * the rest    — compose-only knobs (ports, DB credentials, docker gid) that
#                   the compose file interpolates; they are NOT read by the Go
#                   binaries directly.
#
# SECURITY: never put a real secret in .env.example or commit a populated .env.
# Provider API keys live ONLY in the model-gateway's environment (NFR-SEC-05);
# the orchestrator and the event log never see them.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Provider credentials (model-gateway only)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BOLTROPE_MODELGW_PROVIDER selects the adapter the gateway fronts:
#   stub (default) — the built-in deterministic, network-free demo provider. NO
#                    API key and NO model backend, so `docker compose up` runs a
#                    task out of the box (the keyless DOD-05 path the compose
#                    smoke exercises). DEMO / SMOKE ONLY — it replies with a fixed
#                    scripted message and never calls a tool; NEVER production.
#   openaicompat   — any OpenAI-compatible /v1 endpoint (Ollama, vLLM, LM Studio,
#                    llama.cpp, TGI, LiteLLM). Keyless against a LOCAL endpoint;
#                    set BOLTROPE_MODELGW_OPENAI_BASE_URL below.
#   anthropic | gemini | openai — a hosted provider; requires an API key (see below).
BOLTROPE_MODELGW_PROVIDER=stub

# For openaicompat / openai: the base URL of the endpoint. The default points at
# an Ollama/vLLM running on the HOST (reachable via host.docker.internal, which
# the compose file maps to the host gateway). Only consulted when the provider
# above is openaicompat or openai.
BOLTROPE_MODELGW_OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434/v1

# For a HOSTED provider, set the provider above to anthropic|gemini|openai, then:
#   1) put the key VALUE in the matching variable below, and
#   2) set BOLTROPE_MODELGW_API_KEY_ENV to the NAME of that variable.
# The gateway resolves the value by name through its secrets port (env backend),
# so the key value is never stored in config and never leaves the gateway.
BOLTROPE_MODELGW_API_KEY_ENV=
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
GEMINI_API_KEY=
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# The default model id the orchestrator uses when a Run does not override it.
BOLTROPE_DEFAULT_MODEL=claude-3-5-sonnet-latest

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PostgreSQL (the single source of truth)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Database name created by the postgres image and migrated by boltrope-migrate.
POSTGRES_DB=boltrope

# OWNER / superuser role: boltrope-migrate connects as this to run the DDL and to
# grant the app role a login. The application services do NOT use it.
BOLTROPE_DB_OWNER_USER=boltrope_owner
BOLTROPE_DB_OWNER_PASSWORD=boltrope_owner_pw

# NON-OWNER application role (NOBYPASSRLS): every service connects as this so
# Row-Level Security is enforced (migrations/0003 creates it NOLOGIN; the
# boltrope-grant one-shot adds the login below). Change BOTH the password here
# and keep it in sync — the compose file builds the service DSN from these.
BOLTROPE_DB_APP_USER=boltrope_app
BOLTROPE_DB_APP_PASSWORD=boltrope_app_pw

# The full service DSN is assembled by docker-compose from the values above as:
#   postgres://$BOLTROPE_DB_APP_USER:$BOLTROPE_DB_APP_PASSWORD@postgres:5432/$POSTGRES_DB?sslmode=disable
# Set BOLTROPE_POSTGRES__DSN explicitly only if you point the stack at an
# EXTERNAL Postgres instead of the bundled one (then it overrides the assembled
# value for the services). The PG major version pin is fixed to 16 to match the
# postgres:16 image (NFR-PORT-03; must be >= 13).
# BOLTROPE_POSTGRES__DSN=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Observability (OpenTelemetry)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OTLP/gRPC collector endpoint (host:port). The stack does NOT start a collector;
# point this at your own. An unreachable collector only drops spans/metrics — it
# never blocks an agent turn. Transport security to the collector is disabled in
# dev (the services set BOLTROPE_OTLP__INSECURE=1 for you).
BOLTROPE_OTLP__ENDPOINT=otel:4317

# Minimum slog level: debug | info | warn | error.
BOLTROPE_LOG_LEVEL=info

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Security / identity
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The compose stack runs with BOLTROPE_DEV_INSECURE=1 hard-wired (the static-cert
# mTLS fallback; ADR-0013, NFR-SEC-01). Production uses SPIRE-issued SVIDs and
# MUST leave this unset — see deploy/README.md. The SPIFFE trust domain peers are
# authorized within:
BOLTROPE_TRUST_DOMAIN=boltrope.local

# Client-edge OIDC/bearer validation (FR-API-03). Unused under dev-insecure; set
# these for a production orchestrator that validates real client JWTs.
BOLTROPE_OIDC_ISSUER=
BOLTROPE_OIDC_AUDIENCE=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Tool-runtime sandbox (docker-out-of-docker)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Host docker socket bind-mounted into the tool-runtime so it can launch sibling
# sandbox containers. SECURITY: a mounted docker.sock is root-equivalent on the
# host; dev / single-tenant / trusted-code only (ADR-0005).
BOLTROPE_DOCKER_SOCK=/var/run/docker.sock

# The host's `docker` group GID, so the non-root tool-runtime user may use the
# mounted socket. Find it with:  getent group docker | cut -d: -f3
# On Docker Desktop (macOS/Windows) the socket is typically root-owned; leave 0.
BOLTROPE_DOCKER_GID=0

# Base image the tool-runtime launches for each per-session sandbox. Pre-pull it
# on the host (`docker pull debian:stable-slim`) for a fast first tool call.
BOLTROPE_TOOLRT_IMAGE=debian:stable-slim

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Host port mappings (published by compose)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only the orchestrator is published; model-gateway / tool-runtime / projectord
# stay on the internal network. Change if these clash with something local.
BOLTROPE_ORCH_GRPC_PORT=9000
BOLTROPE_ORCH_HTTP_PORT=8080

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Resource hints & misc
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Per-service CPU / memory limits (compose deploy.resources). Bump for heavier
# local models or larger workloads.
BOLTROPE_SVC_CPUS=1.0
BOLTROPE_SVC_MEMORY=512m

# Sub-agent recursion depth cap (FR-EXT-04).
BOLTROPE_SUBAGENT_MAX_DEPTH=2

# projectord knobs.
BOLTROPE_PROJECTOR_SUBSCRIPTION=cost-rollup
BOLTROPE_PROJECTOR_SWEEP_INTERVAL=5m

# Image tag stamped into built images and binaries (-ldflags main.version).
BOLTROPE_VERSION=dev
